  <description type="morphology">Plants usually glandular, rarely eglandular, usually not canescent. Stems
        unbranched basally, branched distally. Racemes: rachis sparsely to densely pubescent, often
        glandular. Fruiting pedicels divaricate to ascending, forming 20–60(–80)º angle,
        (7–)10–18(–23) mm. Flowers: sepals yellow, 1.5–2.6 mm; petals (1.7–)2–3 × 0.6–1 mm. 2n = 14,
        28.</description>
